{"id":989429259,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"2 months, 2 weeks","timestamp":1688831994,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"2 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/989429259/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Partition String Into Minimum Beautiful Substrings","memory":"40.8 MB","code":"import java.util.Arrays;\n\nclass Solution {\n    public int minimumBeautifulSubstrings(String s) {\n        int n = s.length();\n        int[] dp = new int[n + 1];\n        Arrays.fill(dp, n + 1);\n        dp[0] = 0;\n\n        for (int i = 1; i <= n; i++) {\n            if (s.charAt(i - 1) == '0') {\n                continue;\n            }\n\n            for (int j = 0; j < i; j++) {\n                if (s.charAt(j) == '0') {\n                    continue;\n                }\n\n                long num = extractNumber(s, j, i);\n                if (!isPowerOfFive(num)) {\n                    continue;\n                }\n\n                dp[i] = Math.min(dp[i], dp[j] + 1);\n            }\n        }\n\n        return (dp[n] < n + 1) ? dp[n] : -1;\n    }\n\n    public long extractNumber(String s, int start, int end) {\n        long num = 0;\n        for (int i = start; i < end; i++) {\n            num = num * 2 + (s.charAt(i) - '0');\n        }\n        return num;\n    }\n\n    public boolean isPowerOfFive(long num) {\n        if (num < 125) {\n            return (num == 1 || num == 5 || num == 25);\n        }\n\n        if (num % 125 != 0) {\n            return false;\n        } else {\n            return isPowerOfFive(num / 125);\n        }\n    }\n}\n","compare_result":"","title_slug":"partition-string-into-minimum-beautiful-substrings","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
